  "text": "Excuse me ma'am. Ma'am, question for you. How old were you when you became a millionaire? 28. 28 years old and then how did you get rich? You're not going to ask me when I became a billionaire. Are you serious? Yes. How did you become a billionaire? How did you get rich? Own business. You have to own your business. Yes. So how many companies do you own? I have more than 10 companies around the world. Can I interview you for a minute? Yes, of course. So what was the most amount of money you made in a single year? When I was young, 6 months, $80 million. You made $80 million in 6 months? Yes. What business? IP licensing. Did you come from a lot of money? I started with negative debt of $3 million. You started negative 3 billion. How? My family member passed away and I inherited $3 million in debt, not in cash. For somebody who is stuck in that cycle of poverty, what advice would you give to them? If you want to escape the cycle of poverty, be friends with at least one rich person because all the rich people want to teach you how they become rich. They want to give you some money to start your business. The poor will only bring you down. Did you go to college? Yes. Of course, I had 2 master degree before I was 20 years old. What's one lesson about business that you would teach me right here that is not taught in business school? Okay. A lot of people aim for sale for the figure of the revenue. No, not the revenue, not even profit. Because your profit could be hidden in the bad debts, in the things that you can't get. The most important thing is the net cash that you can take out of the business as the net dividend after tax in your pocket. That's all that's count. That's game right there. Where are you from? My parents are from Thailand, but I live in Monaco. How important is it for an entrepreneur to leave their hometown? It is the best thing. Every time you leave your hometown, it's no longer comfortable. You become enlightened. So it's safe to say that you can't become a billionaire working from home. You're not a tree. You're not a tree. If you're going to sit on the couch, go sit on the couch in Paris. If me and you die tomorrow and you had one more message to leave with the younger generation, what would that be? Remember, don't always try to make people like you. Because when you're successful, you will have haters. You only need to please God. And that's it. Because humans, you can never please them. They can't even please themselves. You have amazing advice. Thank you. I connect with all the billionaires at any of you. Could I get your contact? Yes, of course. I give it to you. Call me anytime.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.3,
      "text": "Excuse me ma'am. Ma'am, question for you."
    },
    {
      "start": 2.5,
      "end": 4.1,
      "text": "How old were you when you became a millionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 4.6,
      "end": 4.9,
      "text": "28."
    },
    {
      "start": 5.2,
      "end": 6.8,
      "text": "28 years old and then how did you get rich?"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.1,
      "end": 9.0,
      "text": "You're not going to ask me when I became a billionaire."
    },
    {
      "start": 9.7,
      "end": 10.2,
      "text": "Are you serious?"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.5,
      "end": 10.5,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 10.7,
      "end": 11.6,
      "text": "How did you become a billionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 11.9,
      "end": 12.5,
      "text": "How did you get rich?"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.6,
      "end": 12.8,
      "text": "Own business."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.1,
      "end": 14.8,
      "text": "You have to own your business."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.1,
      "end": 15.2,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 15.4,
      "end": 16.5,
      "text": "So how many companies do you own?"
    },
    {
      "start": 16.7,
      "end": 18.5,
      "text": "I have more than 10 companies around the world."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.6,
      "end": 19.5,
      "text": "Can I interview you for a minute?"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.7,
      "end": 20.3,
      "text": "Yes, of course."
    },
    {
      "start": 20.4,
      "end": 22.8,
      "text": "So what was the most amount of money you made in a single year?"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.8,
      "end": 24.9,
      "text": "When I was young, 6 months, $80 million."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.5,
      "end": 26.8,
      "text": "You made $80 million in 6 months?"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.9,
      "end": 27.0,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 27.1,
      "end": 27.6,
      "text": "What business?"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.0,
      "end": 28.7,
      "text": "IP licensing."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.7,
      "end": 29.9,
      "text": "Did you come from a lot of money?"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 32.3,
      "text": "I started with negative debt of $3 million."
    },
    {
      "start": 32.9,
      "end": 33.9,
      "text": "You started negative 3 billion."
    },
    {
      "start": 34.0,
      "end": 34.2,
      "text": "How?"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.6,
      "end": 39.2,
      "text": "My family member passed away and I inherited $3 million in debt, not in cash."
    },
    {
      "start": 39.4,
      "end": 42.6,
      "text": "For somebody who is stuck in that cycle of poverty, what advice would you give to them?"
    },
    {
      "start": 42.8,
      "end": 47.8,
      "text": "If you want to escape the cycle of poverty, be friends with at least one rich person"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.8,
      "end": 50.6,
      "text": "because all the rich people want to teach you how they become rich."
    },
    {
      "start": 50.7,
      "end": 52.8,
      "text": "They want to give you some money to start your business."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.0,
      "end": 54.5,
      "text": "The poor will only bring you down."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.7,
      "end": 55.3,
      "text": "Did you go to college?"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.5,
      "end": 55.8,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.8,
      "end": 58.8,
      "text": "Of course, I had 2 master degree before I was 20 years old."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.1,
      "end": 63.1,
      "text": "What's one lesson about business that you would teach me right here that is not taught in business school?"
    },
    {
      "start": 63.2,
      "end": 63.4,
      "text": "Okay."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.6,
      "end": 66.6,
      "text": "A lot of people aim for sale for the figure of the revenue."
    },
    {
      "start": 67.0,
      "end": 69.6,
      "text": "No, not the revenue, not even profit."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.8,
      "end": 74.5,
      "text": "Because your profit could be hidden in the bad debts, in the things that you can't get."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.6,
      "end": 78.0,
      "text": "The most important thing is the net cash that you can take out of the business as"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.0,
      "end": 80.3,
      "text": "the net dividend after tax in your pocket."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.5,
      "end": 81.3,
      "text": "That's all that's count."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.5,
      "end": 82.2,
      "text": "That's game right there."
    },
    {
      "start": 82.4,
      "end": 83.1,
      "text": "Where are you from?"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.3,
      "end": 85.3,
      "text": "My parents are from Thailand, but I live in Monaco."
    },
    {
      "start": 85.3,
      "end": 87.8,
      "text": "How important is it for an entrepreneur to leave their hometown?"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.1,
      "end": 89.4,
      "text": "It is the best thing."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.6,
      "end": 92.6,
      "text": "Every time you leave your hometown, it's no longer comfortable."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.8,
      "end": 93.7,
      "text": "You become enlightened."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.9,
      "end": 96.3,
      "text": "So it's safe to say that you can't become a billionaire working from home."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.4,
      "end": 97.0,
      "text": "You're not a tree."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.3,
      "end": 97.8,
      "text": "You're not a tree."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.0,
      "end": 99.9,
      "text": "If you're going to sit on the couch, go sit on the couch in Paris."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.4,
      "end": 104.2,
      "text": "If me and you die tomorrow and you had one more message to leave with the younger generation, what would that be?"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.4,
      "end": 107.5,
      "text": "Remember, don't always try to make people like you."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.6,
      "end": 109.7,
      "text": "Because when you're successful, you will have haters."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.9,
      "end": 111.4,
      "text": "You only need to please God."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.7,
      "end": 112.2,
      "text": "And that's it."
    },
    {
      "start": 112.4,
      "end": 114.0,
      "text": "Because humans, you can never please them."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.0,
      "end": 116.0,
      "text": "They can't even please themselves."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.2,
      "end": 117.0,
      "text": "You have amazing advice."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.3,
      "end": 117.7,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.8,
      "end": 119.3,
      "text": "I connect with all the billionaires at any of you."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.4,
      "end": 119.9,
      "text": "Could I get your contact?"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.2,
      "end": 120.7,
      "text": "Yes, of course."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.9,
      "end": 121.5,
      "text": "I give it to you."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.6,
      "end": 122.2,
      "text": "Call me anytime."
    }
